[Better a Lie Than a Truth]

2
00:00:02,540 --> 00:00:05,600
[Episode 2]

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:09,400
Look how well we worked together today.

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,790
Would you consider living together?

5
00:00:11,790 --> 00:00:13,700
How about my apartment?

6
00:00:16,930 --> 00:00:18,750
Your smile is a little stiff.

7
00:00:18,750 --> 00:00:21,780
Relax your brow ridge a little, and you'll seem more genuine.

8
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:24,700
I don't want to trouble you either,

9
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,900
but my mom is still a little suspicious.

10
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:29,150
She said that she is going to do something like pay me back in batches.

11
00:00:29,150 --> 00:00:31,620
It will take three months to get my tuition back.

12
00:00:31,620 --> 00:00:33,600
That's none of my business.

13
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,210
Son, I'll come by to see you tomorrow. Someone needs to be home, okay?

14
00:00:42,210 --> 00:00:44,570
Mom, we are both busy tomorrow.

15
00:00:44,570 --> 00:00:47,723
I don't care. Figure something out yourselves.

16
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,470
We can consider living together.

17
00:00:56,470 --> 00:00:58,380
I'll go back and pack now.

18
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:10,100
[Su Nian's Apartment]

19
00:01:18,850 --> 00:01:20,700
This apartment is too small, isn't it?

20
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:22,900
Should I ask the tenant in my apartment on Zhongwu Road to leave?

21
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:24,270
Don't do that.

22
00:01:24,270 --> 00:01:26,200
The two of them just got married,

23
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:28,600
they like small rooms and tiny beds.

24
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:32,680
- It will bring them closer.
- Right, right, closer.

25
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:35,490
By the way, Nian Nian. When are you going to get registered?
(T/N: Registering with the government makes the marriage official)

26
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:39,250
I heard that you can get on the waiting list online through an app.

27
00:01:39,250 --> 00:01:41,800
You should hurry and make an appointment.

28
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:43,700
Er... It's like this mom.

29
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:47,730
Su Nian did a little research, and an auspicious day is three months away.

30
00:01:47,730 --> 00:01:49,200
Right.

31
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,760
We are one family from now on. Tell me if you need anything.

32
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:52,970
Don't be polite.

33
00:01:52,970 --> 00:01:56,130
Mom, I really do need to ask you for something.

34
00:01:56,130 --> 00:01:58,000
I've been trying to get an interview with Qiao Musheng recently.

35
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,540
- Can you make an appointment for me?
- Okay.

36
00:02:01,540 --> 00:02:04,850
My brother is really busy. He doesn't have time.

37
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:06,800
Busy, busy, busy. All he knows how to do is work.

38
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,600
He doesn't have time for his family at all. He's also Nian Nian's brother.

39
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,730
It's nothing. Leave it to me.

40
00:02:11,730 --> 00:02:13,700
Thank you, Mom!

41
00:02:15,390 --> 00:02:17,350
Mom, it's getting late.

42
00:02:17,350 --> 00:02:19,500
You two should go on back and rest.

43
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:22,420
They are going to rest, too. Let's go, let's go.

44
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:24,400
Mom, take care.

45
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,150
You two, don't stay up too late.

46
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:07,050
My female warriors, keep an eye on him for me,

47
00:03:07,050 --> 00:03:09,870
and don't let him pass the boundary line.

48
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:11,770
You don't need to worry about that.

49
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:24,100
"Roommate Rules and Regulations"?

50
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:27,500
After 9pm at night, do not cross the boundary line.
[2. Do not plunder other people's food without consent]

51
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,650
No wait, you really are ridiculous.

52
00:03:29,650 --> 00:03:32,450
What could a girl like me do to you?

53
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:33,750
Lessons learned from the past.

54
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,630
- That day, at the hotel...
- That day...

55
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:38,210
That day I was drunk.

56
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:40,950
Besides, this is my apartment.

57
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:43,100
What can you do even if I don't obey your rules?

58
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,700
Try it.

59
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,100
What did you buy?

60
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,950
Curiosity killed the cat.

61
00:04:01,850 --> 00:04:05,130
Your fish is over the line, make it go back.

62
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,050
Don't you like animals?

63
00:04:11,050 --> 00:04:13,790
Your brother likes animals quite a bit.

64
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:16,798
Especially Goldfish.

65
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,900
You seem to know my brother quite well.

66
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:22,598
Of course I do. We were classmates after all.

67
00:04:22,598 --> 00:04:24,550
Also, he's my interviewee.

68
00:04:24,550 --> 00:04:27,550
Of course I know him very well.

69
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:33,550
Then I'll take good care of it.

70
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,900
You really are fickle.

71
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,650
I got the things you mailed.

72
00:04:54,650 --> 00:04:57,800
So, you really are going to accept the interview today?

73
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,000
She used my mom,

74
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,360
and she knows Qiao Musheng quite a bit.

75
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:05,650
Then be careful.

76
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,320
You're awake!

77
00:05:57,320 --> 00:06:00,150
I made you breakfast. Shall we eat together?

78
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:03,528
You didn't put poison in it, did you?

79
00:06:03,528 --> 00:06:05,900
I acted like that last night because you overreacted first.

80
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,500
I was just going to get some water.

81
00:06:10,150 --> 00:06:12,498
It was my fault yesterday.

82
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,050
Does your hand still hurt?

83
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:16,488
I... I...

84
00:06:16,488 --> 00:06:18,550
Shouldn't I ask about you first?

85
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:21,300
Did I damage your head?

86
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:25,370
I'm not hurting. Not at all.

87
00:06:25,370 --> 00:06:28,698
I just think that since we are roomies now,

88
00:06:28,698 --> 00:06:32,700
then shouldn't we get along in the next three months?

89
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:34,850
Hello, new Roomie.

90
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:36,100
No, that's okay.

91
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:38,400
We are just working together.

92
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,440
I think it's good as it is.

93
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,560
What's wrong?

94
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,960
Nothing.

95
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:03,400
You're a good cook.

96
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,650
Eating like that isn't good for your health.

97
00:07:05,650 --> 00:07:07,650
Why don't you eat what I made?

98
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:29,000
You drew the line and then went ahead to cross it yourself.

99
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:34,720
Oh, right, I'm finally going to interview your brother today.

100
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:38,000
As your roomie, do you have any information to offer?

101
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,200
No, I don't.

102
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,150
You know what his personality is like.

103
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:44,300
Also, we haven't been in touch for a long time.

104
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:48,050
Okay.

105
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:53,150
Do you need to cover the injury on your head?

106
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,500
It's just a minor injury. Nothing serious.

107
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:59,500
The liquid foundation is in the bathroom. Go do it yourself.

108
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:04,940
Stop!

109
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:06,540
What's wrong?

110
00:08:09,550 --> 00:08:12,700
I'm the one who hit you after all. Let me help you.

111
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,100
I'm... going to work.

112
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:00,435
My daughter, are you off to work?

113
00:09:00,435 --> 00:09:02,160
Why are you here?

114
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,400
I came to ask you something today.

115
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:07,292
I heard that you object to me marrying your mom?

116
00:09:07,292 --> 00:09:10,002
I said I object, so I object.

117
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:13,950
Is there some misunderstanding between us? Dad will explain everything.

118
00:09:13,950 --> 00:09:15,800
You pretend to be a small business owner in front of my mom.

119
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,000
But how much gambling debt are you actually hiding?

120
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,900
Who told you that bullshit? That's nonsense!

121
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:24,400
Today, I'm going to do what I can as your father!

122
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,200
What are you doing?

123
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,050
What's your problem?

124
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:36,200
You are not going anywhere today. I'm going to teach you a lesson.

125
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,200
Okay! Let's see what you've got. Run over me!

126
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:55,700
Mr. Qiao, how does it feel to be beaten?

127
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,600
Would you like to give it a try?

128
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,700
No, I'm good.

129
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:02,150
I think I'll just tell Auntie the truth.

130
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:11,050
This is an interview, not a questionnaire.

131
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:13,150
How come none of your answers is more than two words.

132
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:14,835
That should be enough.

133
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:22,700
Editor Su is two hours late already.

134
00:10:23,850 --> 00:10:26,530
Maybe she had a feeling that this wouldn't pay off.

135
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:32,180
- Mr. Qiao, the Elite Official Account has sent someone here.
- Sure.

136
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:33,580
Okay.

137
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:39,380
You? What are you doing here?

138
00:10:39,380 --> 00:10:41,078
What am I doing here?

139
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,050
You should thank me.

140
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:45,670
You are two hours late.

141
00:10:45,670 --> 00:10:48,650
Mr. Qiao's assistant called the Editor-in-chief and asked about it.

142
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:52,250
I was in the neighborhood, so I thought I could do you a favor.

143
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,710
You!

144
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:56,080
If you ask me,

145
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,780
don't fight against me for the training course anymore.

146
00:10:58,780 --> 00:11:01,520
You'll likely never need them.

147
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:30,930
If you're that afraid, why watch it?

148
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:36,150
I... I didn't know you were home. Sorry.

149
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,800
Open the door!

150
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,950
Son-in-law?

151
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:51,300
Is my daughter home?

152
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:53,850
I want to speak to her.

153
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:02,800
Su Nian! Get out here!

154
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,980
What the hell do you want?

155
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,770
Why won't you agree to it?

156
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:12,100
Your mom and I are about to get married. Why are you causing trouble?

157
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:15,500
If you do that again! I'll smash your home to pieces!

158
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:19,800
I'm going to teach you a lesson today!

159
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:39,500
A girl doesn't have to be so tough.

160
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:43,600
If you're not tough, then you'll easily be bullied.

161
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,050
I'm telling you,

162
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:48,400
your brother wouldn't say anything when he was bullied back then.

163
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:51,300
I was the one who stood up for him.

164
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:53,500
That is a bit impressive.

165
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,100
Any other injuries?

166
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:06,200
That guy hit you really hard.

167
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,550
That's not from this time.

168
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:11,100
I got this when I dressed up as a monster,

169
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,340
and tried to interview your brother.

170
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:19,400
Mr. Qiao. Mr. Qiao.

171
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,940
Forget it, it's fine. It's fine.

172
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:49,139
- I'm fine.
- It doesn't hurt.

173
