00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,720
A girl doesn't have to be so tough.

175
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,600
Your brother wouldn't say anything when he was bullied back then.

176
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,499
I was the one who stood up for him.

177
00:14:13,499 --> 00:14:17,300
[Eight Years Ago]

178
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,400
Why are all the fish dead?

179
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:27,780
Qiao Musheng! You killed all the fish!

180
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:32,900
- How brutal is that!
- That's right!

181
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:36,498
- What's going on here?
- Teacher. He killed all the fish.

182
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,350
Qiao Musheng, come with me.

183
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:41,750
Teacher!

184
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,800
Qiao Musheng didn't do it.

185
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,200
How do you know?

186
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,100
I got here first. The fish were already dead when I got here.

187
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:51,800
- I was just looking for you, but I couldn't find you.
- Is that so?

188
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:57,850
Teacher, Su Nian probably just wants to help Qiao Musheng out of this

189
00:14:57,850 --> 00:15:01,900
- because they are close.
- Right?

190
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:06,060
Qiao Musheng is such a weirdo.

191
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:07,880
There's nothing that he wouldn't do.

192
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:14,160
Liu Xing... Liu Xing!

193
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,950
She's getting physical!

194
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:17,750
Look at her, Teacher!

195
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:22,897
They were wrongly accusing you. Why didn't you say something?

196
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:24,980
Too much trouble.

197
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,280
[The Day Before]

198
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:31,500
Students, remember to cut off the water and electricity when you leave.

199
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,380
Okay.

200
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:52,320
Editor-in-chief, just give me one more chance.

201
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:54,700
You aren't embarrassed to ask for another chance?

202
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:57,780
Don't you know how late you were for the interview with Qiao Musheng?

203
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:59,800
Fortunately, Xiao Meng was there to take care of it.

204
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:02,750
Right now, the company has decided to deduct your bonus for a month

205
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:05,840
and cancel your qualification for the training course.

206
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,820
I can accept deducting my bonus for a month,

207
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:10,240
but why cancel my qualification for training course?

208
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,900
Why?

209
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,750
You were so late for the interview,

210
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,750
and Mr. Qiao was incredibly displeased.

211
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:19,720
Our leadership learned about it, and they think you are damaging our company's image!

212
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,320
So...

213
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,878
Reflect on it yourself!

214
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:26,310
Editor-in-chief, it was my fault that I was late yesterday.

215
00:16:26,310 --> 00:16:29,900
But the entire outline for the interview was mine.

216
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:31,382
Yours?

217
00:16:31,382 --> 00:16:34,900
The company pays you every month.

218
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:39,000
Your work naturally belongs to the company!

219
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:44,300
So who has the qualification for the training course?

220
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,500
It's Xiao Meng for now.

221
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,400
If you really think this isn't fair,

222
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:52,348
how do people say it...

223
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:54,860
"The world gives me grief,

224
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:57,520
but I respond with a song."

225
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:59,480
I don't have such a big heart.

226
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:02,560
The world gives me grief, and I'll respond with a slap.

227
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:34,400
- Hello, Mom...
- Nian,

228
00:17:35,007 --> 00:17:38,400
you child, you finally turned your cellphone on.

229
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:41,100
I just had it repaired.

230
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:44,000
What's going on with you? How could you hit Uncle Fang?

231
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Mom, I'm telling you. He isn't a good person.

232
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,550
Don't say that.

233
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:50,798
He treats me so nicely.

234
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,950
He cares about me every day.

235
00:17:52,950 --> 00:17:54,380
And he's not angry with you anymore.

236
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:57,650
I bought him a new pair of shoes to make him feel better.

237
00:17:57,650 --> 00:17:59,560
Remember to transfer the money to me.

238
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:02,450
I spent that money for your sake.

239
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,250
Mr. Qiao, since your stomach hurts,

240
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,637
why don't we skip the dinner meeting tonight?

241
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:21,660
[Mom]

242
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:26,300
Mom.

243
00:18:26,308 --> 00:18:29,000
Do you know where Xiao Jingnian went?

244
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,150
I called him so many times,

245
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:33,650
and I just can't get through.

246
00:18:36,042 --> 00:18:37,918
Hello? Hello?

247
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:40,400
Mom, don't worry.

248
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:43,050
He probably just forgot to bring his phone.

249
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:44,450
It has been a long time already,

250
00:18:44,450 --> 00:18:46,500
he wasn't like this before.

251
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,950
I learned how to pay phone bills online, and I charged a lot, but I still can't get through.

252
00:18:49,950 --> 00:18:52,098
Can you go look for him?

253
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:54,350
Mom, don't worry.

254
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:55,750
Nothing will happen to him.

255
00:18:55,750 --> 00:18:58,150
- I'm...
- How could you be so cold-blooded?

256
00:18:58,150 --> 00:18:59,450
It's about your brother.

257
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:01,930
Aren't you worried even a little?

258
00:19:01,930 --> 00:19:04,580
I really raised you for nothing!

259
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:10,100
Auntie rarely calls. Is it urgent?

260
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:12,790
Turn the car around and head back to the office.

261
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:23,848
Mom, I went out today and lost myself.

262
00:19:23,848 --> 00:19:26,250
I didn't even notice that my cellphone had died.

263
00:19:26,250 --> 00:19:27,850
It's okay. It's okay.

264
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:30,550
Okay.

265
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:49,139
Tell Mr. Liu that we'll be there later.

266
00:19:49,139 --> 00:19:51,000
You are still going?

267
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,700
Mr. Qiao.

268
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:18,900
Mr. Qiao. I'm sorry! I shouldn't have been late!

269
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,700
Since you know that you made a mistake,

270
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:22,780
then you should live with the consequences.

271
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:29,000
Can you, because we were classmates once,

272
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,100
give me another chance?

273
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:35,000
I really can't lose this opportunity for the training course.

274
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,260
I don't know what you're talking about.

275
00:20:40,350 --> 00:20:42,950
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to do it on purpose.

276
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:46,550
My... my mom's boyfriend broke my cellphone.

277
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:49,100
I was riding a scooter to the office and also fell,

278
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:50,850
I really didn't mean to be late.

279
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:53,500
Can you give me another chance?

280
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,530
That has nothing to do with me.

281
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:59,050
Qiao Musheng, how did you become this person?

282
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,550
This is who I've always been.

283
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:05,450
No! You weren't like this.

284
00:21:05,450 --> 00:21:09,600
When we were in school, there was a goldfish in our classroom.

285
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:12,650
You were the only one who had been taking care of it until the end.

286
00:21:12,650 --> 00:21:13,900
Because you wanted to know

287
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:18,500
why people liked the goldfish and then why they didn't.

288
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:21,298
You wanted to know what that felt like

289
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:24,050
because you couldn't feel it.

290
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:28,100
But one day, the goldfish died.

291
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:31,100
You opened the oxygen pump and tried to save them,

292
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,900
because you didn't want to lose them.

293
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:37,650
They all said that you... you were a monster without feelings.

294
00:21:37,650 --> 00:21:39,650
But... But you aren't.

295
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:42,350
You do have feelings.

296
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:44,300
Are you done yet?

297
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:47,500
Just give me another chance!

298
00:21:48,650 --> 00:21:50,800
I can't do that.

299
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:06,660
You fail at everything.

300
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:09,600
What right do you have to get promoted?

301
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:24,700
Why did you come back?

302
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:27,150
Leave me alone!

303
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:28,750
I was just late that one time.

304
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:32,200
Does the company really have to treat me like that?

305
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:35,150
I really helped you for nothing back then!

306
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,840
I'm not leaving! I'm not leaving!

307
00:22:43,350 --> 00:22:45,550
I'm not leaving!

308
00:22:50,150 --> 00:22:52,200
I'm not leaving!

309
00:23:21,420 --> 00:23:23,330
[Daily Note]

310
00:23:37,020 --> 00:23:39,160
[Q and A: Boss Qiao's Secret Path]

311
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:01,400
Find out what happened to her at work.

312
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,900
Okay.

313
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,700
I can't sleep yet.

314
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:12,040
I haven't cleaned my make-up off yet. I haven't cleaned my make-up off yet.

315
00:24:39,907 --> 00:24:43,247
Your skin ages ten days if you fall asleep with your make-up on.

316
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:12,698
I am just like Unlucky's mother opening the door for Unlucky.

317
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:15,350
Welcoming Unlucky home!

318
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:19,998
Tell me... why?

319
00:25:19,998 --> 00:25:23,698
Why do others' efforts always pay off

320
00:25:23,700 --> 00:25:29,013
and it is only me that fails and fails?

321
00:25:30,100 --> 00:25:33,300
It'll be all right. Things will be all right.

322
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,100
You still have me, don't you?

323
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:41,350
Heartbreaker.

324
00:25:41,350 --> 00:25:43,900
Don't say things like that.

325
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:48,600
Our agreement ends in three months.

326
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:55,198
When that time comes, no one will remove my make-up for me.

327
00:25:56,950 --> 00:25:59,850
Then what do I need to do for you to stop crying?

328
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,300
I don't know!

329
00:26:06,750 --> 00:26:10,050
I'm hopeless.

330
00:26:40,900 --> 00:26:43,940
♫ It's a miracle that we met ♫

331
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:47,798
♫ Like two parallel lines intertwined ♫

332
